                    Act II: Identify paragraphs.

                    Scene @FLIP_PREP: Romeo and Puck enter; seed Puck's bottom sentinel.

[Enter Romeo and Puck]

Romeo: You are as good as a pig!
Romeo: Remember yourself!

                    Scene @FLIP: Pop Romeo, push onto Puck until sentinel.

Puck: Recall your past!
Puck: Are you as good as a pig?
Puck: If so, let us proceed to scene @SEED.
Romeo: You are as good as me!
Romeo: Remember yourself!
Puck: Let us return to scene @FLIP.

                    Scene @SEED: Swap Romeo for Hamlet; seed sentinel; detect blockquote.

[Exit Romeo]
[Enter Hamlet]

Puck: You are as good as a pig!
Puck: Remember yourself!

Hamlet: Recall your past!
Hamlet: Are you as good as the difference between a big big big big big big cat and a big cat?
Hamlet: If so, let us proceed to scene @SEED_BQ_SPACE.

Hamlet: Remember yourself!
Puck: You are as good as a cat!
Puck: Remember yourself!
Puck: You are as good as nothing!
Hamlet: Let us return to scene @CONSUME.

                    Scene @SEED_BQ_SPACE: Consumed '>'; try to also consume one following space.

Hamlet: Recall your past!
Hamlet: Are you as good as a big big big big big cat?
Hamlet: If so, let us proceed to scene @SEED_BQ_EMIT.

Hamlet: Remember yourself!

